.TH "tomoyo_init_log" 9 "tomoyo_init_log" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
tomoyo_init_log \- Allocate buffer for audit logs.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "char *" tomoyo_init_log
.BI "(struct tomoyo_request_info *r "  ","
.BI "int len "  ","
.BI "const char *fmt "  ","
.BI "va_list args "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "r" 12
Pointer to "struct tomoyo_request_info".
.IP "len" 12
Buffer size needed for \fIfmt\fP and \fIargs\fP.
.IP "fmt" 12
The \fBprintf\fP's format string.
.IP "args" 12
va_list structure for \fIfmt\fP.
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Returns pointer to allocated memory.

This function uses \fBkzalloc\fP, so caller must \fBkfree\fP if this function
didn't return NULL.
